<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p>Fortune! Prosperity! This is the 6th year of Kōvirājakesarivarman. For Mahādeva of the holy shrine <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>śrīkōyil</foreign></supplied> of the southern side <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tenvāyi &gt; tenvāyil</foreign></supplied> of the temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gṛhattu</foreign></supplied> of the Lord <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>īśvara</foreign></supplied> [of] Avanikantaṟppa, a <foreign>devadāna</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, the daughter of god <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tēvaṉār makaḷār</foreign></supplied> of this temple <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ittaḷi</foreign></supplied>, wife/queen <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>deviyār</foreign></supplied> of Piḷḷai Cēramāṉār, Nakkaṉ Akkāra Naṅkaiyār, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> to burn (<foreign>eri </foreign>&gt; <foreign>eriya</foreign>) night and day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iravum pakalum</foreign></supplied>, as long as the moon and the sun last <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cantrādittavaṟ</foreign></supplied>, one perpetual lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nondāviḷakku oṉṟiṉukku</foreign></supplied>; [she] placed <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 12 <foreign>kalañcu</foreign>s of gold <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>poṉ</foreign></supplied> to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied> one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ney</foreign></supplied> everyday <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied> with this <foreign>uḻakku</foreign>-measure <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>paṭi uḻakkiṉāl</foreign></supplied>; for this lamp to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ivviḷakkeriya</foreign></supplied>, [she] gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 215 standard weight <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>niṟai</foreign></supplied> for one standing lamp <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tirāviḷakkoṉṟu</foreign></supplied>, 215 by the <foreign>ceruviṭai</foreign> measure <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>ceruviṭaiyāl</foreign></supplied> including <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>uḷpaṭa</foreign></supplied> iron <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>iruppu</foreign></supplied> and led <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nārāyam</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

